snippet.textDisplay: Constructed by Landgrave William IV from 1584 to 1618 in Schmalken Thuringer the Schloss Wilhelmsburg is a palace made out of white stones on the outer construction and wood in the inside. It was used as a noble palace with a church and a ball room however today it is a museum that is open from Tuesday to Sunday, from 10 am to 4pm, the price to get in as an adult is 6 euros, as a child 4 euros, in a group of 10 it would cost 5 euros a person and finally as a family it is 12 euros. The castle is know for it's garden, it's beutiful decoration and it hosts one of the oldest protestant church.

snippet.textDisplay:
Some notes:
1. Nix the red light serial-killer background lights. Clear some of the junk off the wall , it looked frankly messy.
2. Josh is being lost in the sheer size of the kitchen. I suggest switching to the old kitchen. He seems way more comfortable in a smaller quieter space.
3. The whole shoot seemed rushed. Sssslllllooooowwwww the F down. Josh's best clips are thoughtfully paced out and measured making use of his sardonic wit.
4. Only x1 assistant during the shoot. He is talking to both. which is distracting to him and the audience.
5. Josh seems best when he has a straight man (in the comidic sense) to work with. Even better if that person is female , someone to gaffow at his usual off-the-cuff remarks. Emily Fleming comes to mind. They have excellent working chemistry.

All in all decent clip, just needs work. Josh is superb as allways.
